 checkpoint support for Cursor agent in IDE and CLI. Note: resume and rewind are missing for now ([#392](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/392), [#493](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/493), [#525](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/525), [#527](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/527))\\n    13→- Consolidated E2E test suite moved into `e2e/` with per-agent filtering, transient error retry, preflight checks, and test report generation ([#474](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/474), [#508](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/508), [#539](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/539))\\n    14→- Agent integration Claude skill for multi-phase agent onboarding ([#498](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/498))\\n    15→- Post-commit cache to avoid redundant work on consecutive commits ([#500](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/500))\\n    16→- `entire enable` now creates local metadata branch from remote when available, preserving checkpoints on fresh clones ([#511](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/511))\\n    17→- `entire --version` now works as an alias for `entire version` ([#526](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/526))\\n    18→- Mise linting to keep `mise.toml` clean; scripts moved into task files ([#530](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/530))\\n    19→- `commit_linking` setting replaces the Strategy interface abstraction, with `[Y/n/a]` prompt on commit ([#531](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/531))\\n    20→\\n    21→### Changed\\n    22→\\n    23→- Extracted magic numbers to named constants ([#276](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/276))\\n    24→- Removed auto-commit strategy entirely, making manual-commit the only strategy ([#405](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/405))\\n    25→- Upgraded to Go 1.26 and golangci-lint 2.10.1 ([#458](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/458))\\n    26→- O(depth) tree surgery replaces O(N) flatten-and-rebuild for both metadata branch and shadow branch writes ([#473](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/473), [#503](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/503))\\n    27→- Renamed `paths.RepoRoot()` to `paths.WorktreeRoot()` for clarity ([#486](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/486))\\n    28→- Local and CI linting now use the same configuration ([#504](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/504))\\n    29→- Consistent context.Context threading through all function call chains (~25 `context.Background()`/`context.TODO()` replaced) ([#507](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/507), [#512](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/512))\\n    30→- Unified `CalculateTokenUsage` into a single `agent.CalculateTokenUsage()` function ([#509](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/509))\\n    31→- Removed backward-compatibility fallbacks for unknown agent types ([#515](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/515))\\n    32→- Removed Strategy interface abstraction — `ManualCommitStrategy` is now used directly everywhere ([#531](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/531))\\n    33→- Replaced `fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr)` with structured logging in agent hook paths ([#538](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/538))\\n    34→- Moved `AgentName` and `AgentType` to `agent/types` package to break import cycle ([#542](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/542))\\n    35→\\n    36→### Fixed\\n    37→\\n    38→- Carry-forward false positive when user replaces agent content before committing ([#502](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/502))\\n    39→- Isolate integration tests from global git config ([#513](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/513))\\n    40→- Using OpenCode with Codex models now correctly handle `apply_patch` events ([#521](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/521))\\n    41→- Compaction resetting transcript offset, causing Gemini carry-forward to re-send already-condensed content ([#535](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/535))\\n    42→- Handle OpenCode `database is locked` errors during parallel E2E tests ([#540](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/540))\\n    43→\\n    44→### Docs\\n    45→\\n    46→- Agent integration guide and checklist updated for Cursor and OpenCode ([#410](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/410), [#510](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/510))\\n    47→- E2E test README and debug skill ([#474](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/474))\\n    48→- Cursor agent documentation ([#493](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/493), [#525](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/525))\\n    49→\\n    50→### Thanks\\n    51→\\n    52→Thanks to @ishaan812 for contributing to this release!\\n    53→\\n    54→Thanks to @9bany ([#260](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/260)) for their Cursor PR! We've now merged our Cursor integration. While we went with our own implementation, your PR were valuable in helping us validate our design choices and ensure we covered the right scenarios. We appreciate the effort you put into this!\\n    55→\\n    56→## [0.4.7] - 2026-02-24\\n    57→\\n    58→### Fixed\\n    59→\\n    60→- Commits hanging for up to 3s per session while waiting for transcript updates that were already flushed ([#482](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/482))\\n    61→\\n    62→### Housekeeping\\n    63→\\n    64→- Updated README to include OpenCode in the supported agent list ([#476](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/476))\\n    65→\\n    66→## [0.4.6] - 2026-02-24\\n    67→\\n    68→### Added\\n    69→\\n    70→- OpenCode agent support with resume, rewind, and session transcripts ([#415](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/415), [#428](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/428), [#439](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/439), [#445](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/445), [#461](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/461), [#465](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/465))\\n    71→- `IsPreview()` on Agent interface to replace hardcoded name checks ([#412](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/412))\\n    72→- Stale session file cleanup ([#438](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/438))\\n    73→- Redesigned `entire status` with styled output and session cards ([#448](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/448))\\n    74→- Benchmark utilities for performance testing ([#449](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/449))\\n    75→\\n    76→### Changed\\n    77→\\n    78→- Refactored Agent interface: moved hook methods to `HookSupport`, removed unused methods ([#360](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/360), [#425](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/425), [#427](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/427), [#429](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/429))\\n    79→- `entire enable` now uses multi-select for agent selection with re-run awareness ([#362](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/362), [#443](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/443))\\n    80→- Use Anthropic API key for Claude Code agent detection ([#396](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/396))\\n    81→- Don't track gitignored files in session metadata ([#426](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/426))\\n    82→- Performance optimizations for `entire status` and `entire enable`: cached git paths, pure Go git operations, reftable support ([#436](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/436), [#454](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/454))\\n    83→- Streamlined `entire enable` setup flow with display names and iterative agent handling ([#440](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/440))\\n    84→- Git hooks are now a no-op if Entire is not enabled in the repo ([#445](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/445))\\n    85→- Resume sessions now sorted by creation time ascending ([#447](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/447))\\n    86→\\n    87→### Fixed\\n    88→\\n    89→- Secret redaction hardened across all checkpoint persistence paths ([#395](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/395))\\n    90→- Gemini session restore following latest Gemini pattern ([#403](https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/403))\\n    91→- Transcript path stored in checkpoint metadata breaking location independence ([#403](https://github.com/